{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.20",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 20 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:1",
      "text": "Then Sophar the Naamathite answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:2",
      "text": "Therefore various thoughts succeed one another in me, and my mind is hurried away to different things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:3",
      "text": "The doctrine with which thou reprovest me, I will hear, and the spirit of my understanding shall answer for me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:4",
      "text": "This I know from the beginning, since man was placed upon the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:5",
      "text": "That the praise of the wicked is short, and the joy of the hypocrite but for a moment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:6",
      "text": "If his pride mount up even to heaven, and his head touch the clouds:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:7",
      "text": "In the end he shall be destroyed like a dunghill, and they that had seen him, shall say: Where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:8",
      "text": "As a dream that fleeth away he shall not be found, he shall pass as a vision of the night:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:9",
      "text": "The eyes that had seen him, shall see him no more, neither shall his place any more behold him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:10",
      "text": "His children shall be oppressed with want, and his hands shall render to him his sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:11",
      "text": "His bones shall be filled with the vices of his youth, and they shall sleep with him in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:12",
      "text": "For when evil shall be sweet in his mouth, he will hide it under his tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:13",
      "text": "He will spare it, and not leave it, and will hide it in his throat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:14",
      "text": "His bread in his belly shall be turned into the gall of asps within him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:15",
      "text": "The riches which he hath swallowed, he shall vomit up, and God shall draw them out of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:16",
      "text": "He shall suck the head of asps, and the viper's tongue shall kill him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:17",
      "text": "Let him not see the streams of the river, the brooks of honey and of butter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:18",
      "text": "He shall be punished for all that he did, and yet shall not be consumed: according to the multitude of his devices so also shall he suffer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:19",
      "text": "Because he broke in and stripped the poor: he hath violently taken away a house which he did not build.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:20",
      "text": "And yet his belly was not filled: and when he hath the things he coveted, he shall not be able to possess them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:21",
      "text": "There was nothing left of his meat, and therefore nothing shall continue of his goods:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:22",
      "text": "When he shall be filled, he shall be straitened, he shall burn, and every sorrow shall fall upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:23",
      "text": "May his belly be filled, that God may send forth the wrath of his indignation upon him, and rain down his war upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:24",
      "text": "He shall flee from weapons of iron, and shall fall upon a bow of brass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:25",
      "text": "The sword is drawn out, and cometh forth from its scabbard, and glittereth in his bitterness: the terrible ones shall go and come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:26",
      "text": "All darkness is hid in his secret places: a fire that is not kindled shall devour him, he shall be afflicted when left in his tabernacle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:27",
      "text": "The heavens shall reveal his iniquity, and the earth shall rise up against him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:28",
      "text": "The offspring of his house shall be exposed, he shall be pulled down in the day of God's wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.20.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 20:29",
      "text": "This is the portion of a wicked man from God, and the inheritance of his doings from the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
